50|$|The Mano {{machine is}} a {{computer}} theoretically described by M. Morris Mano. It contains a central processing unit, random access memory, and an <b>input-output</b> <b>bus.</b> Its limited instruction set and small address space limit it {{to use as a}} Microcontroller. But it can easily be expanded to have a 32-bit accumulator register, and 28-bit addressing using a HDL language like Verilog or VHDL; And at the same time, make room for new instructions.|$|E

